<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter    
38</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>O 
lord, rebuke me not in thy wrath: neither chasten me in thy hot displeasure.</P>
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>For thine arrows  
stick fast in me, and thy hand presseth me sore.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD           
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>There is no soundness in my flesh   
because of thine anger; neither is there any rest in my bones because of my     
sin.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>For mine  
iniquities are gone over mine head: as an heavy burden they are too heavy for   
me.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>My wounds  
stink and are corrupt because of my foolishness.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD           
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>I am troubled; I am bowed down      
greatly; I go mourning all the day long.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A     
NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>For my loins are filled with a loathsome disease: 
and there is no soundness in my flesh.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>I am feeble and sore broken: I have roared by     
reason of the disquietness of my heart.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A      
NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>ADONAY, all my desire is before thee; and my      
groaning is not hid from thee.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4> 
10</H4></TD><TD><P>My heart panteth, my strength faileth me: as for the light   
of mine eyes, it also is gone from me.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>My lovers and my friends stand aloof from my    
sore; and my kinsmen stand afar off.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A         
NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>They also that seek after my life lay snares    
for me: and they that seek my hurt speak mischievous things, and imagine        
deceits all the day long.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4>      
13</H4></TD><TD><P>But I, as a deaf man, heard not; and I was as a dumb man     
that openeth not his mouth.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>    
14</H4></TD><TD><P>Thus I was as a man that heareth not, and in whose mouth are 
no reproofs.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P>
For in thee, O YHVH, do I hope: thou wilt hear, O ADONAY my ELOHIYM.</P></TD>   
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>For I said, Hear me, 
lest otherwise they should rejoice over me: when my foot slippeth, they magnify 
themselves against me.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4>  
</TD><TD><P>For I am ready to halt, and my sorrow is continually before me.</P> 
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>18</H4></TD><TD><P>For I will      
declare mine iniquity; I will be sorry for my sin.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD         
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V19><H4>19</H4></TD><TD><P>But mine enemies are lively, and  
they are strong: and they that hate me wrongfully are multiplied.</P></TD></TR> 
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V20><H4>20</H4></TD><TD><P>They also that render     
evil for good are mine adversaries; because I follow the thing that good is.</P>
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V21><H4>21</H4></TD><TD><P>Forsake me not, 
O YHVH: O my ELOHIYM, be not far from me.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A    
NAME=V22><H4>22</H4></TD><TD><P>Make haste to help me, O ADONAY my              
salvation.</P></TD></TR></TABLE><!--This Software is copyright 2000 by John M.  
